    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate prioritizing stolen base upside and favorable matchup volatility. **Corbin Carroll** (87.14) is our clear cornerstone play; he benefits from a plus-matchup against Burke and, crucially, a slow pitcher delivery that maximizes his elite speed profile. He is joined at the top of the board by **James Wood** (78.42) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.75). Both players capitalize on favorable park factors in their respective matchups, with **Mickey Moniak** specifically gaining a massive 14% efficiency boost from a dynamic platoon advantage against V\u00e1squez. **Brice Turang** and **Trevor Story** also provide high-floor production, with the latter exploiting an exploitable 5.74 xERA from Gil to cement his spot in the lineup.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision was the exclusion of **Alex Freeland** (49.73), who narrowly missed the cut behind the stability of **Jose Caballero**. While **Alex Freeland** offers switch-hitting versatility, his #9 spot in the order significantly depressed his ceiling relative to our middle-infield starters. We are also keeping high-upside bats like **Giancarlo Stanton** and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** on the bench, as their platoon disadvantages against a tough arm in Early (2.34 xERA) made them inefficient starts for today\u2019s specific game-cap environment. \n\nA final note of caution: **Dalton Rushing** is currently our most fragile asset. While his 56.46 score keeps him in the lineup, the 42% rain risk in his matchup creates immediate exposure to early-game truncation. Should that game be delayed or impacted, we are prepared to pivot, though we remain confident that his pairing with **Vinnie Pasquantino**\u2014who is primed for a strong day with a 14% platoon boost\u2014will keep our offense moving. We are effectively managing our roster depth, keeping **Max Muncy** and others ready should conditions shift or late-breaking injury news emerge.",
